## Unit 1 Day 1-2: What Is a Computer?

First, let's explore the first lesson in the curriculum. To begin, find your ECS your curriculum and open to page 28.

<a href="http://www.exploringcs.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/ExploringComputerScience-v5.0.pdf#page=28" target="_blank">Access a digital copy of the lesson >></a>

#### Key Concepts

1. Identify computers in non-traditional items (<i>coffee makers, digital watches, cars...</i>)

1. Discuss and critique other students' ideas (<i>this unit is largely based on discussion - enforcing good discussion strategies will help students succeed</i>)

#### Common Difficulties

It is critical to encourage discussion in this lesson. It sets the stage for the entire course. Use this as an opportunity to start planning and sharing techniques to facilitate discussion.

